name: red kidney bean production | red kidney bean | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/26814/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 tonne of dried red kidney bean (<15% moisture) during May-September, 2020. The amounts of flows are weighted averages over all existing local crop production datasets available for this specific product.

Starting inputs for this activity include seed, fertilizer, crop protection products and fuel on the farm. This activity begins with soil preparation about 39 weeks after the harvest of the previous crop. The soil is prepared for cultivation in last week of May and the sowing of seeds started about 5 days after soil preparation.

This activity ends with navy bean drying to <15% moisture at farm gate. This takes place in September, 17 weeks after the activity starts. The activity includes the infrastructures and use of agricultural machinery.

Physical (mass) allocation; N credits from biological N fixation are included as a system expansion, consistent with the ISO 14044 multifunctionality hierarchy. A negative input was included of ammonia N fertilizer to represent amount of N fixed.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/011:Growing of non-perennial crops/0111:Growing of cereals (except rice), leguminous crops and oil seeds

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Soil cultivating date for the main crop: May 2020; Harvesting date for the main crop: September 2020. Total time from the date of sowing to the date of harvesting comes to 17 weeks. Yield data were collected and averaged for three crop cycles (2018-2020). All other data were collected for 2020 only.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: CA-ON, CA-MB.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Production of red kidney bean includes farm practices from tillage, fertilizer application, pre-plant herbicide application, planting, rolling, post-emergent herbicide application, inter-row cultivating/scuffing/hilling, fungicide application, pre-harvest desiccation, pull/undercut/knife, windrow/swathing, harvesting, and other field activities, to aeration and drying.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName. Weights are based on production volumes. CA-ON: production volume = 4.76e+06 kg/year, weight = 0.6049 CA-MB: production volume = 3.11e+06 kg/year, weight = 0.3951 The uncertainty information has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Site-specific field data were collected via survey from prairie province red kidney bean producers for crop rotation, seeding rate, machinery and fuel use for field operations (e.g., tillage, harrowing, harvest), farm inputs (e.g., fertilizers, pesticides), and electricity for crop drying. Production weighted averages were calculated for the region. Outliers were removed from reported fuel use data based on visual inspection.

exchanges.description: Global average LUC emissions according 2nd edition of the Quantis-modified tool developed by Blonk Consultants 'WFLDB-adapted-Blonk 2014 direct-land-use-change-assessment-tool_2015-05-18a.xlsx', tab. 'Country & land use unknown'. The emission are based on the relative change in production areas in all countries for a given crop. The weighted average is used which takes into acount relative difference in crop expansion into primary forest, secondary forest, grassland, perennial and annual land. The amount of 0.95 tonne of CO2 per ha*year (taken from the tool) is divided with the yield per ha. Extrapolated crop: beans, dry.
